On 11/23/03 7:12 AM, "scott lyons" <slyons(-at-)netrover.com> wrote:

> Make sure it is the copper
> type and check the temperature rating. The anti-sieze from Wurth is rated to
> 1200 degrees, there is one made by permatex and probably others as well.

Everything Wurth makes is excellent and so is 3M. I use 3M brake
Lube/Anti-Seize (#08945). Don't let the name fool you: it's copper
anti-seize and rated to 1800F.

http://homepage.mac.com/ratwell/.Pictures/Maintenance2/198-3M08945.jpg

Good stuff for the star adjusters in the drum brakes.

